did.abstract: The collection contains 26 boxes of files created by Joe Szabo in the production of "Witty World" magazine and other publications related to cartoon art.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of Materials
arrangement.p: The Joe Szabo Papers and Collection of Original Comic Art has been preliminary arranged and minimally processed and described, mostly at the box level. Files are alphabetical by artist's last name or by geographic location.

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Materials
separatedmaterial.p: Original art has been separated out and will be cataloged in the Original Art Database. Please check the Original Art Database for updates. Uncataloged original art from this collection is available to researchers, please contact the reading room at cartoons@osu.edu or call 614-292-0538.

Books and other published materials have also been separated out. It will be cataloged in the Ohio State Libraries Catalog under the collection ns2:title "Joe Szabo Papers and Collection of Original Comic Art." Please check the catalog for additions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection contains files created by Joe Szabo in the production of "Witty World" magazine and other publications related to cartoon art. It has been minimally processed at the box level and preliminarly arranged alaphatically by artists' last name, subject matter, and geographic location. The folder titles were named by Szabo.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Joseph George Szabo, born February 4, 1950 in Budapest, Hungary. He graduated from the Academy of Journalism in 1974. In 1980, he and his wife emigrated to the United States to escape Communism in Hungary. They settled in North Wales, PA. Joe worked as a freelance cartoonist for a time. In 1987, he found the magazine "Witty World" which chronicled cartooning from around the world. Szabo also launched a variety of print and electronic publications related to cartoon art. He passed away on February 2, 2016 at his home in North Wales, PA.
